Source:  First Past the Post
Author:  PHILLIPS
Vol / Page:  89
Edition:
Quote:  By the late 1870s a monster in the form of the totalisator (primitive as it was at that stage) raised its head to leer in the direction of the bookies. The warning became louder in 1879 when the Wellingtonc orrespondent of the <i>Lyttelton Times</i> telegraphed:'... that it is proposed to amend the Lotteries Act so as to legalise the totalisator"... In 1880 a Mr Ekberg patented an elementary type of totalisator which was first used at the Canterbury Jockey Club in that year.
Notes:  Miriam Redwood "I lay the Field" in <Proud Silk</i> 1979

