Date:  0/6/2005
Source:  NZ Memories
Author:
Vol / Page:  No 54, p. 46
Edition:
Quote:  There are suggestions that there were some early primitive totalisator machines in operation in Auckland and Australia, but the credit for the first mechanized totalisator in the world goes to a Mr. Ekberg of Christchurch who invented and patented a mechanical totalisator in 1880.  ... It was first used in Riccarton by [47] the Canterbury Jockey Club. ... Public opposition continued to flourish and in 1896 a Bill to abolish the totalisator was narrowly defeated.
